rComments: She's a great prof and was able to make ethics material engaging and thought provoking. I'd certainly recommend her because I genuinely felt like I learned something when most ethics classes are bs. She's not an overly tough grader but you'll need to invest a bit more effort if you want the A.
Awful experience with this prof. She simply does not care about her students , and it shows in everything she does. Avoid at all costs.

Lazar is an awesome prof. Exciting lectures, interesting reading material and provoking assignments! I've never been passionate about a class until now. She brought in two guest speakers which allowed us to ask questions to professionals in the HR field. If your program is ECH u likely have background knowledge, if not, get ready to learn a lot

Teacher is not approachable. Does not facilitate discussions really well. Seems genuinely uninterested in the development of her students. The content of the course is good but the structures of lectures are not designed to help student understand. Expectations are not clear.

Really makes a content heavy lecture move quickly. Informative, interesting, and funny. The readings are heavy but you can get away without doing them all so long as you're able to pinpoint what content is most important. Exams are tough but fair. Mini group projects of 5% throughout the semester. Would take again but she isn't a bird course prof.

It is almost impossible to do well in her class. She does not want to see her students excel. As a result, the class average tends to always be around a B. She provides no feedback to her students and takes off marks for the most absurd reasons. The class was poorly organized and heavily based on presentations and minimum input from her.

Great prof who is upbeat and brings a refreshing vibe to University studies. Extremely intelligent and brought in some brilliant guests who were prestigious and full of insight. Young professor who cares about her students and although is intense/expects a lot, she makes the class enjoyable!
